description:
Job Duties:


Handle out-patient and in-patient precertification or case approvals;
Liaise with doctors, other service providers, and internal business units to gather information pertinent to a particular case;
Conduct case reviews/follow up if necessary;
Handle medical claims related issues and enquiries;
Deliver professional customer service to the network, clients, and other service providers;
Take on other assignments as required 

Requirements & Attributes:


Holder of Bachelor’s Degree;
3 years of experience in health care management, medical or insurance claims;
Good communication skills in both English and Chinese including Putonghua;
Excellent customer service skills;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office;
Candidates with higher qualifications or more experience will be considered for the position of Senior Officer;
Immediately available is an advantage

We offer regular working hours, friendly work environment, and a competitive remuneration package to the right candidate commensurate with his/her qualifications and working experience.  Fringe benefits include medical schemes (including eligible dependants), discretionary performance-based bonus, birthday leave, etc.


Applicants should send their C. V. with expected salary & availability to HR at DoctorVio.com or by clicking "Apply Now".

Major responsibilities:

Managing claims handling inquiry; coverage determination, quantum analysis, and legal liability assessment, where appropriate within authority limits;
Demonstrating a basic standard of technical claims competence for handling all Property & Liability Insurance claims;
Meet service turnaround time and achieve claims KPI targets;
Participate in-service meetings with client groups;
Provide quality customer services and handle a complaint;
Assist in reviewing workflow, implementing continuous claims process improvement;
Assist in compiling regular management reports;
Handle ad hoc projects such as systems enhancement and ad hoc reporting.

Qualification and Experience Requirement:


Degree holder or tertiary graduate with professional qualifications in insurance or related disciplines;
2 – 5 years’ Property & Liability insurance claims handling experience;
Customer-oriented with good communication and interpersonal skills;
Good team player, able to work independently and under pressure;
Result-oriented, self-motivated, analytical, and detailed-minded in problem-solving;
Strong sense of responsibility with a high level of integrity and trust;
Good command of English and Chinese in both written and spoken;
Sound PC skills in MS Word, Excel & Chinese word processing;
For strong candidates with less experience will be considered for an Officer position.

Major responsibilities:


Assist Assistant Claims Manager to support the team in daily claims operation;
Assess and approve Employees Compensation Insurance claims within authority limits;
Striving for continuous improvement on claim file handling;
Meet service turnaround time and achieve claims KPI targets;
Participate in-service meetings with client groups;
Provide quality customer services and handle a complaint;
Assist in reviewing workflow, implementing continuous claims process improvement;
Assist in compiling regular management reports;
Handle ad hoc projects such as systems enhancement and ad hoc reporting.

Qualification and Experience Requirement:


Degree holder or tertiary graduate with professional qualifications in insurance or related disciplines;
2 – 5 years’ Employees Compensation insurance claims handling experience;
Customer-oriented with good communication and interpersonal skills;
Good team player, able to work independently and under pressure;
Result-oriented, self-motivated, analytical, and detailed-minded in problem-solving;
Strong sense of responsibility with a high level of integrity and trust;
Good command of English and Chinese in both written and spoken;
Sound PC skills in MS Word, Excel & Chinese word processing.
For strong candidates with less experience will be considered for an Officer position.

Key Responsibilities:

Formulate and implement Employee Benefits claims strategy and development plan to achieve the company objectives for profitability and growth;
Monitor & approve claims within the pre-set authority and provide appropriate commentary, recommendations and justifications to senior management to seek for approval when necessary; 
Manage and supervise the daily operations of the Employee Benefits claims team;
Complaint handling and resolving disputes;
Develop high quality work teams with clear accountabilities and performance expectations to ensure ability to deliver high performance;
Actively improve processes and efficiency using service benchmarks and analytical data;
Implement the Group compliance policy to adhere the relevant local and Group compliance procedures and obtain satisfactory audit and regulators’ review reports;
Engage in continuing education and training opportunities when possible.
Manage ad hoc projects as required.

Key Requirements:

Degree holder and preferably with insurance-related qualifications, e.g. FLMI, ICA, ACII/ANZIIF;
Minimum 10 years’ experience in medical & life claims and with 5+ years in managerial positions;
Understand the impact of market forces and regulatory issues on the insurance industry;
Can compare the company's insurance practices to other organizations;
Can describe key industry benchmarks and relate them to own organization or functional specialty;
Hold digital mindset and able to initiate & implement technology and processes changes;
Strong analytical and problem solving, self-motivated, excellent interpersonal and communication skills;
Good team player and self-starter; able to interact with people at all levels;
Ability to be multi-task and work under pressure;
Strong sense of responsibility with high level of integrity and trust;
Good command of English and Chinese in both written and spoken;
Sound PC skills in MS Word, Excel and power point;
Knowledge of FDA health regulations.

We offer 5-day work, good career prospects and attractive remuneration package to the right candidates. Interested parties please send full resume with expected salary to: The Human Resources Department, 21/F, Cityplaza One,1111 King’s Road, Taikoo Shing, Hong Kong or by email.

Personal data collected will be strictly used for recruitment purpose only. All unsuccessful applications will be destroyed after two years

